At least one person was reported to have drowned during the flash floods on the N3 in Linksfield. The heavy downpour also affected air traffic out of OR Tambo International Airport were delayed yesterday due to the stormy weather that hit the area hard yesterday.People took to social media to post pictures of cars submerged in water which let to traffic chaos around Johannesburg and on scene Emer-G-Med paramedics reported that on the N3 Linksfield about 70 cars were submerged with others pushed off the road.